{"id":"project-LICHEN-tr8q","title":"BLE transport: potential NULL dereference in connected_cb","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/ble_ipsp_transport.c
Lines: 121-127

After calling bt_conn_get_info(), the code accesses info.le.data_len->tx_max_len without checking if data_len is NULL:

    if (bt_conn_get_info(conn, &info) == 0) {
        transport_state.mtu = info.le.data_len->tx_max_len;
        ...
    }

The data_len field can be NULL if the connection doesn't have LE Data Length extension negotiated (BLE 4.0 connections). This will cause a NULL pointer dereference on older BLE devices.

Fix: Check if info.le.data_len != NULL before dereferencing.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:53:20.40077Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:53:20.400804Z"}
